This paper deals with the development of a new method to improve the prediction consistency and accuracy of vortex-induced vibrations (VIV) in marine risers. The approach involves the use of adaptive hydrodynamic parameters and data clustering algorithms. While the paper is not directly related to computer science, it involves the use of computational methods and algorithms for data analysis and optimization. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.RO (Robotics), and cs.MS (Mathematical Software).
